											amā-re
										, stem amā-; 
											monē-re
										, stem monē-; 
											teg&ebreve;-re
										, stem teg&ebreve;-; 
											audī-re
										, stem audī-.

The active forms vāpulō , vāpulāre, be flogged, and vēneō, vēnīre, be sold (contracted from vēnum īre, go to sale), have a passive meaning, and are sometimes called neutral passives. To these may be added fierī, to be made (§ 204), and exsulāre, to be banished (live in exile); cf. accēdere, to be added. The following verbs are sometimes found as semi-deponents: iūrō , iūrāre . iūrātus, swear;
nūbō , nūbere , nūpta, marry;
placeō , placēre , placitus, please.

